       fhir:definition [ fhir:v "The repeated period in a cyclical schedule (of one or more dosing instructions). A cyclic schedule is noted in days, the corresponding dosing duration is also in days.\r\n\r\nExamples of a cyclical schedule: contraceptive pill (21 days, 1 pill 1x a day, then skip for 7 days, repeat), repeat period here is 28 days.\r\nRepeatPeriodCyclicalSchedule" ] ;
